deck: Son of Kirith & Rhialdor, brother of Barmek
description:
Jormak is slightly taller than his younger brother Barmek. He has long coal-black hair that is tightly drawn back and threaded through seashells giving it the appearance of a long braid. His eyes are a deep golden-brown and quite piercing. Jormak has a strong and powerful physique which he maintains through disciplined sporting activities. He tends to be self-absorbed and has complete disregard for the values and feelings of others. He is very much into the physical, not given to contemplation or development of his inner resources. He is the lead hunter with a fascination for inventing weapons for defence and conquest. He is cunning and shrewd and can be manipulative at times, and certainly not be laughed at for it would raise his wrath. With dark rugged looks and an intense sexual aggression, he is popular with many of the Wave Dancers.

After Winnowill left, Jormak became close with Sleia and they opted to have their legs fused into tails.

description:
Sleia has a well-toned body for a female elf and is shorter than the average Wave Dancer. She has crystal blue eyes and light sandy-brown hair which she keeps braided. She has a square jaw, a broad nose and strong forehead. Sleia is not known as a pretty elf, but what she lacks in looks is made up tenfold in courage and personality. She can be wilful and cheeky, and is very nimble. She is Barmek's best friend, and is loyal, honesty and trustworthy. Quiet and a little reserved around most of the others, she blossoms into a gregarious and delightful personality when she is adventuring with Barmek. She can be humorous, outgoing and talkative and is the more practical of the two. Sleia can move with great stealth, and is very comfortable with her body and her sporting prowess.

Rejected by Barmek, Sleia and Jormek become lovers and opt to have their legs fused into tails.

deck: Lili is a fairy with a crush on Jerom.
description:
Origin

Lili and her sisters Lala and Lolo are more than 800 years old. On Earth, they came into contact with Lambik and Jerom when several children had disappeared after they had bought specific balloons that were made by the fairies. Lili explained to Jerom that she and her sisters had created the balloons so that the children could inflate them with their breath. The balloons were then to magically return to the fairies, so they could use the youthful breaths contained in the balloons to stay young. But a design flaw in the balloons caused the children to disappear and some were turned into mushrooms. Before they could undo their wrongs, Lili and her sister were called back to Phantazia, their homeworld. Sus Antigoon convinced the fairy queen to transform the children back to their true forms.

She later returned to Earth to create a fairytale land for Jerom and his friends.
name: Lili

deck: Kanae Katagiri is a Gemischt Quincy servant of the Ishida family, who married Ryuken and was the mother of Uryu.
description:
Origin

Kanae Katagiri is a Gemischt Quincy, mixed breed, who was brought to be a servant of the pure-blooded Ishida Family, and more specifically the guard of their only son, Ryuken Ishida, Over the years as his servant, she feel in love with Ryuken, but never acted upon her feelings.

Creation

Kanae Katagiri (片桐 叶絵, Katagiri Kanae) is a supporting character of the BLEACH series that was created by Tite Kubo, It first began serialization Shueisha's Weekly Shonen Jump in August 2001. She was first introduced during the flashback portion of the The Thousand-Year Blood War Arc that began in Volume 59.

She first appeared in BLEACH Volume 59 CH. 530 "Everything But the Rain op.3 'Dark of the Moon'".

Major Story Arcs

The Thousand-Year Blood War Arc

Masaki Kurosaki had been brought to the Ishida household after her parents had died. As a pure-blood Quincy, she was there to one day marry Ryuken. Katagiri tried to play supportive since it meant the continuation of the Ishida line. Katagiri joined Ryuken to follow Misaki when he ran off to fight a Hollow and save a Soul Reaper on her own. Misaki had won the fight by the time they arrived, but she had been bitten. Katagiri defied Ryuken's orders to keep the incident a secret and reported it to his mother. When Ryuken confronted her about it, she said it was for the future of the Quincy, what he said he wanted. Ryuken took the infected Masaki and ran from the house.

Katagiri followed later and found Ryuken. He had left Masaki with the Soul Reaper, Isshin Shiba, to save. When Ryuken sounded as if he would leave the Ishida Family, she begged him not to be sad or think of himself as weak. Seeing him sad breaks her heart. She swore she would always be by his side. Over the following years, Ryuken and Katagiri were married and they had one son. Uryu Ishida. Nine years later, on June 17, Katagiri lost consciousness and passed away, since Yhwach used Auswahlen to steal the power of every Gemischt Quincy for himself.

Powers & Abilities

Spiritual Awareness

As with most Quincy, Katagiri has a unique set of abilities that she can use in a fight. Along with an enhanced spiritual awareness comes the ability to manipulate Reishi (spirit particles) energy into weapons, such as arrows of light.

Spirit Weapons

Quincy have the ability to manipulate Reishi into weapons made of spiritual energy. This is nearly always formed into bows and arrows.

Blut

Blut (血装 (ブルート), Burūto) is a special defensive technique of the Quincy. This power is in the very blood of all Quincy, and using it gives them super human defense and offensive powers. It's performed by directing the flow of Reishi directly into the blood vessels. This risk is that once used it prevents a Quincy from using their light arrows. As a mixed-breed, Katagiri obtained this power through training.
name: Kanae Katagiri

deck: The True Crown
description:
Raenafel is a fourth generation Wave Dancer and is destined to be the fourth Crown by her birthright. Brom and Ailsa are Raenafel's parents, and she was born a Child of Recognition. She stands taller than the average female WaveDancer, and can look most male elves in the eye. She has extremely long thick hair the colour of midnight, and her plush deep purple eyes are doe-like in appearance. In contrast to the other elves, Raenafel is a babe in the woods and knows nothing of the world except for what she learn from Brom's, Kirith's and No-Wing's teachings when she was hidden away. Despite her naivety and her lack of socialisation, she has tremendous powers: healing and flesh-shaping. Raenafel is a natural leader and does not shirk at the threat of danger, and she takes her role as the next Crown very seriously.

Raenafel recognized Barmek when he was a squirt and upon her rescue by him and Sleia, they consumated their primal urge. They had a daughter and chose to raise her together as lifemates.

description:
Sydor, the High One, is very tall and gangly in appearance. He has cobalt blue eyes and his hair is frosted creme. He is silent and lethal in his actions, and is a dark character who has split inside himself. He lives in secrecy waiting patiently for the time when he can change all and sundry into their original forms and return to the skies in the palace. He mismanages his magic, and uses his flesh-shaping abilities to inflict pain on the innocent even though he is convinced that he is doing the right thing. Sydor also has the ability to black send and to create a bubble around him that refracts light and therefore appears invisible under water.

Sydor's true name is Rydos and suffers from a split personality. Sydor was the one known to the Wave Dancers as the Cursemaker who stole their children of Recognition, while Rydos is the side Irralee recognizes.

deck: Sabo is the Chief of Staff for the Revolutionary Army with the powers of the Flame-Flame Fruit. He's the brother of Luffy and Ace.
description:
Origin

Sabo was the child of a noble family in the Gao Kingdom on Dawn Island in the East Blue. His own family treated him as a tool to marry and increase his family's social standing and wealth. Fed up, he ran away to be an orphan in Grey Terminal. His first friend was Ace, and later came Luffy. The three would become closer than any friends and celebrated their brotherhood with three cups of saki.

However, Sabo's father had hired the Bluejam Pirates to force him to return by threatening the lives of Ace and Luffy. Sabo returned to his family home, but discovered not long after that the nobles had planned to burn out all the poor from Grey Terminal with firebombs. He was unable to warn or stop the firebombing, and he didn't know the fate of Ace and Luffy. He still wrote a letter for Ace and had it delivered to Curly Dadan's home.

Longing to finally be free, Sabo set sail on his own, but his boat was shot out of the water by one of the Celestial Dragons in his passing vessel. He was thought to be dead by all who witnessed the attack, but he had been rescued by Monkey D. Dragon, the leader of the Revolutionary Army.

Creation

Sabo (サボ, Sabo) is a supporting character in the One Piece series that was created by Eiichiro Oda. The series first began serialization in Shueisha's Weekly Shōnen Jump on August 4, 1997. He first appeared during the Dawn Island Arc that began in Volume 59.

His first appearance was in One Piece Volume 59 CH. 583 "Gray Terminal - The Final Destination of the Uncertainty".

Character Evolution

Major Story Arcs

Dressrosa Arc

Sabo had been working from the shadows in the Revolutionary Army for years, but he arrived on Dressrosa with Koala just as Luffy and his Straw Hats were attacking Don Quixote Doflamingo's group. He met with him at Corrida Colosseum, and took on his persona of "Lucy" in the tournament to claim Ace's Flame-Flame Fruit.

One Piece (1999)

The One Piece animated series is a direct adaptation of Oda's original manga.. It's produced by TOEI Animation and first began airing in October 20, 1999. Sabo's first anime appearance was in One Piece - Episode 494 "Here Comes Sabo! The Boy at the Gray Terminal!", which aired on April 17, 2011 in Japan. His standard Japanese voice actress is Junko Takeuchi, For the U.S. dub produced by FUNimation has yet to announce a voice actress.

deck: Shakuyaku "Shakky" is a former pirate and now proprietor of Shakky's Rip-Off Bar in Sabaody Archipelago.
description:
Origin

Shakuyaku, Shakky, is a former pirate that even clashed with the hero of the Marine Vice-Admiral Garp, but she gave up the wild life for the straight and narrow for unknown reasons. She eventually retired into hiding at Sabaody Archipelago to open up a bar called Shakky's Rip-Off Bar. A friend and frequent patron to her establishment was the former first-mate of the Roger Pirates, Silvers Rayleigh. She befriended a former empress of Amazon Lily, Gloriosa; and they took in three young Kuja Amazons who had escaped slavery from the Holy Land Marie Jois under the cruel Celestial Dragons. Gloriosa eventually took Hancock, Sandersonia, and Marigold back to Amazon Lily in the Calm Belt. When Rayleigh was saved from drowning by a child fish-man named Hatchan, he would drop by Shakky's bar to visit, and she always welcomed him.

Though retired, Shakky follows the news on up and coming pirates. Though the names of several rookies stood out in the papers. One crew caught her interest, and more so the captain, Monkey D. Luffy. She admired the trouble he caused without getting innocent people involved. That made her a fan of his.

Creation

Shakuyaku (シャクヤク, Shakuyaku) is a supporting character in the One Piece series that was created by Eiichiro Oda. The series first began serialization in Shueisha's Weekly Shōnen Jump on August 4, 1997. She would later appear in the Sabaody Archipelago Arc that began in Volume 50.

Her first appearance was in One Piece Volume 51 CH. 498 "The Eleven Supernovas" She's more often referred to by her nickname "Shakky" (シャッキー, Shakkī).

Though she was a pirate forty years ago. Her actual age is unclear. The name Shakuyaku comes from the Japanese word (芍薬) for the Chinese peony.

Major Story Arcs

Sabaody Archipelago Arc

Shakky was surprised when Hatchan arrived one day, along with the mermaid Camie and several members of the Straw Hat Pirates. They were looking for Rayleigh to get their ship coated. She surprised Luffy by knowing about many of his exploits, and she told them about the Eleven Supernovas. She told them she hasn't seen Rayliegh in months, but gave them some clues on where to look.

The group returned later with Rayleigh, but Htachan had been shot by one of the Celestial Dragons. Shakky stayed to listen as Rayleigh told the Straw Hats the truth about Gold Roger's supposed capture by the Navy. Shakky distributed Vivre Cards to the Straw Hats so they could go into hiding while Rayleigh worked on the coating. However. Rayleigh returned with news that the Straw Hats had been defeated yet saved by the intervention of the Warlord, Bartholomew Kuma. Kuma met with Rayleigh and Shakky's bar later to tell him where he had sent the pirates.

Dawn Island Arc

After the end of the Paramount War, Rayleigh was busy trying to figure out how Luffy had gotten from Amazon Lily to Marineford to be involved in the war. He knew of Boa Hancock's hatred toward men. It was Shakky who suggested that Hancock had fallen in love with Luffy. Rayleigh went to Amazon Lily to investigate, and Shakky watched over the Straw Hat's pirate ship with Hatchan, Camie, and the leader of the Rosy Life Riders, Duval. Bartholomew Kuma later arrived to take over the duties of watching the Thousand Sunny.

Fish-Man Island Arc

Two years had passed since she last met the Straw Hat Pirates. Rayleigh had returned six months before then from training Luffy in the use of Haki. Roronoa Zoro was the first to return. The crew reunited, and they left on their ship to Fish-Man Island.

Powers & Abilities

Shakky's powers and abilities are unknown. She was at one time a pirate of enough reputation to have clashed with Monkey D. Garp. and she can beat up anyone who refuses to pay her prices.

Other Media

Anime

One Piece (1999)

The One Piece animated series is a direct adaptation of Oda's original manga.. It's produced by TOEI Animation and first began airing in October 20, 1999. Shakky's first anime appearance was in One Piece - Episode 392 "New Rivals Gather! The 11 Supernovas", which aired in March 8, 2009. Her character in the Japanese series is voiced by Hiromi Tsuru, and the U.S. dub produced by FUNimation has yet to announce a voice actress.

deck: A robot with the personality of Doctor Doom programmed to attack New York City during Civil War, he was defeated by the Avengers and kept in Hank Pym's lab. In the aftermath of Age of Ultron, he was given the chance to redeem himself.
description:
Note: this is a page for the Doombot character featured in Avengers A.I., for all other Doombots use the Doombots team page.

Character Creation

Doombot first appeared in Civil War #2. He was created by Mark Millar and Steve McNiven. Like all Doombots, this one also thinks he is the real Doctor Doom, saying that it is beneath him to save innocent lives and constantly shouting "I am Doom!" when attacking.

Major Story Arcs

Marvel NOW!

In Marvel NOW! Doombot is in the care of Hank Pym, who has recreated the A.I. to work for him. He's currently a member of the artificial intelligence team of Avengers. If the robot turns against the team, Pym will activate the micro black hole that was implanted in Doombot's chest. Though Vision has been worrisome to Doombot's presence, he has shown great power in the mission where they rescued a hospital from S.H.I.E.L.D.-drones that were possessed by a new A.I., Dimitrios, that Hank Pym released when he defeated Ultron.

Powers & Abilities

Doombot possesses a great amount of strength, being able to destroy heavy objects. He acquires flight through the use of jets under his feet. Doombot also possesses the ability to shoot strong power blasts. Like other Doombots he is not easily destroyed and can heal himself by reconstructing limbs. Like the original, Doombot is very intelligent.
name: Doombot

deck: First Generation Wave Dancer
description:
Tentus is the only first generation elf still alive in the WaveDancer colony, and possesses the ability of rock/coral shaping. He is the younger half-brother of Neama, and the child of Ausra and Desh. He is medium in height and has a receding hairline of white hair, bushy eyebrows and his skin has a jaundiced look to it as if it has been stretched over bone. His most prominent features are his grey eyes that look as if they have cataracts. He is somewhat eccentric, a little cranky and impatient because all he wants is to be left alone. His function is the colony is that of historian and he sculpts coral statues of the ancestors and their stories in the Chamber of Remembrance. Tentus is a strong sender and receiver. When the threat of the Soul Stealer is upon them, he can sense it through nightmares which leave him drained, sick and helpless.

He's also Shardon's Uncle through his brother's recognition with Ailsa.
